{
  "texts": [
    "Essentially, the problem is split into two parts: a dynamic model is learned from data, and the model is used to design a controller, with some variations, with model predictive control being a popular choice.",
    "Similarly, in traditional control applications, learned models are incorporated into modern control synthesis techniques, and standard methods of proving safety are adjusted to incorporate learned models.",
    "A learning-based approach that has proved to mesh particularly well with this approach uses Gaussian process models (Akametalu et al., 2014; Umlauft et al., 2017; Wang et al., 2018; Devonport et al., 2020 Devonport et al.,, 2021b)).",
    "Another point of contact is the use of statistical guarantees for controllers based on learned models.",
    "In RL, statistical guarantees of correctness such as regret bounds and probably approximately correct (PAC) bounds are used to ensure that optimal behavior is attained with high probability."
  ]
}